{"message":"The Mays Faculty Guidelines (October 2025) do not address the AACSB Scholarly Academic classification directly. The guidelines reference AACSB standards and expectations in several contexts such as faculty qualifications, intellectual contributions, and the scholarly practitioner classification but they do not define or explain the Scholarly Academic classification itself.

For the definition and criteria of AACSB's Scholarly Academic classification, you would need to consult AACSB accreditation standards documents directly.

Source: Mays Faculty Guidelines, October 17, 2025 (Approved version)."}
